						<div class="postbody">I think pretty much all racing games on the Mega Drive used HBlank interrupts for that very same reason (and of course hills are quite commonplace). Using palette rolling doesn't look smooth so games just change the <span class="posthilit">vertical</span> scroll position every <span class="posthilit">line</span> (and then there's OutRun 2019 abusing both tilemap planes like crazy...).</div>

